A locals guide to Colombia

13 years ago Colombia still had a fairly negative image around the world. With it’s political/economic problems there were not many tourists who visited. Colombia and Miami had one of the largest cocaine connection. This is hardly the case anymore, the torrent of immigration and “expatization”( I made this word up, please don’t laugh)…

Colombia Visa – How to apply

Did you know that there are nearly 21 visa types that Colombia offers? If you needed that many to travel to the US, you would need 93 for Brazil, 50 for Argentina, 51 for Peru and 13 in total for Ecuador. Here is a breakdown of the categories of visas that Colombia offers, including what…

Getting Your Colombian Visa

In order for American Citizens to stay and live in Colombia legally, they must obtain a visa. The only way to obtain a Colombian visa is by visiting the Avisa office in Bogota or at a Consulate in the US. Avisa is the Colombian entity responsible for handling visas. Visas are only issued to foreign nationals for legitimate business purposes…
